The paper discusses Bayesian model averaging and ensemble methods for classification, which are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of compression coefficients and the comparison to previous classifiers suggest a focus on algorithmic and computational aspects, which could also fit in the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.DM). The mention of non-naive classifiers and probabilistic predictions could indicate a focus on neural networks or other types of models used in computational neuroscience (cs.NE) or signal processing (cs.SI).
